<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPTALK; 
</P>
<P>
KEEPING THE DUDLEY DO-RIGHT THING ALIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHLOE ROSS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEEN-AGE NINJA TURTLES and an animated brat named Bart may be all the rage, but 
they'll never replace Rocky and friends in the hearts of baby boomers. 
</P>
<P>
The Dudley Do-Right Emporium, in operation since 1971, features Bullwinkle any 
way you want him -- bendable, hugable, wearable. If you love your fairy tales 
fractured, there are copies of scripts ($8) and story boards ($11.95) from 
creator Jay Ward's collection, as well as rare animation cels from the original 
cartoons ($100 to $350). 
</P>
<P>
Dudley Do-Right Emporium, 8200 Sunset Blvd., Los Angeles; (213) 656-6550. CHLOE 
ROSS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Rocky and Bullwinkle products Sidney Cooper 
