<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
AT HOME; 
</P>
<P>
ALL THE VEGGIES IN ONE BASKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"WHAT'S harvested yesterday is delivered to you today," promises Malibu Greens 
owner Tracey Athanassiadis, referring to her colorful 15-pound seasonal gift 
baskets. 
</P>
<P>
The lush summer basket (available year-round) overflows with an assortment of 
at least 15 baby vegetables -- squash, eggplant, Lollorosso red lettuce, mizuna 
(a Japanese leafy green), leeks, purple and green kohlrabi, carrots, fennel and 
arugula, among them. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the vegetables are raised in Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
The baskets themselves, made of natural straw with handles, come wrapped in 
clear cellophane crowned by a big bow. The baby-vegetable basket sells for $38; 
the deluxe gourmet basket (a combination of vegetables and exotic fruits) runs 
$89. 
</P>
<P>
And for those yearning for an island getaway, Malibu Greens puts together a 
fruit basket ($55) that houses an assortment of exotic fruits -- papayas, 
mangoes, kiwis, passion fruit, Asian pears, persimmons, pomegranates and baby 
pineapples and coconuts -- from around the world. Malibu Greens delivers 
anywhere in the continental United States. 
</P>
<P>
Malibu Greens, (213) 456-5661 or (800) 383-1414, to order. LINDA ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Vegetables Sidney Cooper 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
