<HEADLINE>
<P>
SYLVESTER STALLONE, A MAN OF LETTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It just can't be a coincidence anymore. First there was "Rocky." Then there was 
"Rambo" and "Cobra." Now, it seems that Sylvester Stallone is doing yet another 
one-word title movie named after a five-lettered protagonist, "Oscar" 
(mentioned in the Sept. 16 Movie Chart column). 
</P>
<P>
He should stop beating around the bush and call all of his movies exactly what 
they are: MONEY! 
</P>
<P>
It is also interesting to note that if you replace the m in Rambo with a C and 
rearrange the letters you get Cobra; and if you replace the b in Cobra with an 
s and rearrange the letters you get Oscar. This means the pattern is to replace 
the middle letter and rearrange the letters. Since this means that the c must 
now go, I predict his next film will replace it with a t and become "Ratso." 
</P>
<P>
PETER OLIPHANT 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
