<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUILDING TRADE SHOW SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of exhibits, panel discussions and educational seminars will highlight 
the second annual Building Industry Show, to be held Oct. 24-26 at the Los 
Angeles Convention Center. 
</P>
<P>
The trade is sponsored by the Building Industry Assn. of Southern California 
and co-sponsored by The Times and the National Assn. of Home Builders. 
</P>
<P>
New products, services and technologies will be on display at the convention's 
45,000-square-foot exhibit hall on Oct. 24 from noon to 6 p.m.; on Oct. 25, 
from 10:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. and on Oct. 26 from 8:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Building professionals and the general public are invited to the show. One-day 
passes to the exhibition are $10 for members and $15 for non-members. 
Preregistration fees to attend both the trade show and the seminars range from 
$63 to $125, depending on how many days each visitor attends. 
</P>
<P>
More information can be obtained from the Building Industry Assn. of Southern 
California's headquarters in Diamond Bar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
