<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTERN ATHLETIC ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WYOMING STAYS UNBEATEN WITH WIN OVER AIR FORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wyoming quarterback Tom Corontzos completed 16 of 24 passes for 200 yards and 
connected on touchdown pass plays of 48 and 25 yards to lead the Cowboys to a 
24-12 victory over Air Force in a Western Athletic Conference game Saturday at 
Laramie, Wyo. 
</P>
<P>
Wyoming, 4-0 overall and 1-0 in the WAC, scored its final touchdown on a 
five-yard run by tailback Jay Daffer with less than two minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
Air Force (2-2, 1-2) scored on a two-yard run by DeShawn Durham and a 
seven-yard interception return by Shanon Yates. 
</P>
<P>
Colorado State 38, Texas El Paso 20 -- Brian Copeland rushed for 142 yards and 
a touchdown and set up another score with a 55-yard run as the Rams (3-1, 2-0) 
beat the Miners (1-3, 0-2) in a WAC game at Fort Collins, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
Colorado State spotted UTEP a 13-0 lead three minutes into the game, then 
scored for touchdowns on four consecutive possessions. 
</P>
<P>
Fullback Todd Yert scored twice, and tailbacks Copeland and Tony Alford also 
scored -- all on one-yard runs. 
</P>
<P>
Hawaii 19, Utah 7 -- Garrett Gabriel connected with Jeff Sydner on a 73-yard 
scoring pass to open the fourth quarter, securing the Rainbows' first victory 
in a WAC game at Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
Gabriel completed 18 of 28 passes for 328 yards for the Rainbows (1-2, 1-1). 
Sydner had eight receptions for 131 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Brad Foster scored the only touchdown for Utah (2-2, 0-1) with a one-yard run 
in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Texas Tech 34, New Mexico 32 -- Lin Elliott kicked a 37-yard field goal with 24 
seconds left to give the Red Raiders (1-2) a nonconference victory over the 
Lobos (1-3) at Albuquerque, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
New Mexico (1-3) rallied for three touchdowns in the fourth quarter behind 
quarterback Jeremy Leach, who completed 23 of 54 passes for 349 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Texas Tech quarterback Robert Hall, a freshman, completed 15 of 31 passes for 
316 yards and touchdowns of 37 and 54 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
