<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: DIRECTOR CHOSEN FOR CAL POLY LANDLAB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Edwin Barnes, a Cal Poly Pomona specialist in plant and soil sciences, has been 
appointed director of LandLab, a 339-acre center at the university for 
education and research in the sustainable use of resources. 
</P>
<P>
Barnes has been acting director of LandLab for two years. Previously, he was 
associate director of International Programs at Cal Poly. As a plant and soil 
sciences professor, Barnes also served as a consultant to the Consortium for 
International Development's horticulture improvement project in Yemen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
