<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: CAL POLY EDUCATOR NAMED TO TEST PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Edward Walton, associate professor of chemistry at Cal Poly Pomona, has been 
appointed to the national College Board Committee that develops the Chemistry 
Achievement Test for the Admissions Testing Program. 
</P>
<P>
Walton, who has taught chemistry at Cal Poly since 1987, also designed and 
teaches a course at Cal Poly's School of Education on how science should be 
taught in elementary school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
