<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPERVISORS, AIRPORT OFFICIALS BUFFETED BY TRAVELER TURBULENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What an ingenious idea that the Orange County Board of Supervisors has come up 
with! It can solve the problem of overcrowding at John Wayne Airport, as well 
as having to locate a new airport site, merely by closing the Main Street 
parking lot and forcing everyone to use the airport parking structures at $14 
for each of the first two days and $7 for every day thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
The natural result is that a lot of people such as myself will revert to using 
LAX, leaving John Wayne for the businessmen and women, whose companies will 
reimburse them for their parking expense. 
</P>
<P>
I'd like to add that I am an airline employee who can fly much more cheaply out 
of LAX, and have willingly paid extra money to utilize John Wayne, but I have 
been priced out of this market. 
</P>
<P>
I also have the feeling that after the 90-day "trial period," the remote lot 
will be quietly closed. How much will it cost to use the parking structure 
then? $15? 
</P>
<P>
K. HOOVER 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
