<P>
ENROLLMENT JUMPS 7% AT VENTURA COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ventura College's enrollment for the fall semester has jumped by more than 7% 
over last year, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Registration figures show that 12,393 students have enrolled, a 7.14% increase 
over the 11,567 students who enrolled by mid-September, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
"We believe the increase in enrollment can be attributed in part to the rising 
cost of an education at the university level," said John Woolley, vice 
president for student services. "Ventura College has proven itself to be very 
affordable." 
</P>
