MAN KILLS HIMSELF AFTER SHOOTING HIS EX-WIFE IN QUARREL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 61-year-old man shot and killed himself after wounding his ex-wife wife 
during what police said was a domestic quarrel. 
</P>
<P>
Reza Rostami was found dead in a back entryway of his home in the 4700 block of 
Winvale Avenue on Saturday afternoon with a single gunshot wound to the head. 
</P>
<P>
His ex-wife, Tina Rostami, 40, was listed in good condition at Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana with a gunshot wound to the lower abdomen. 
</P>
<P>
Police, who were called to the home about 12:20 p.m. Saturday, said the ex-wife 
had dropped by Reza Rostami's home, and shortly after her arrival the quarrel 
began. 
</P>
<P>
Police investigator Pete Linton said Reza Rostami then pulled a handgun and 
shot Tina Rostami while she was in the kitchen. He said the man retreated to 
the rear of the house where he turned the gun on himself. 
</P>
<P>
"She (the ex-wife) came over, and they got cranked up over something," Linton 
said. "The matter just boiled over. It's very unfortunate. It's something that 
could happen to a lot of people at any time." 
</P>
<P>
Linton said police were still trying to determine what started the quarrel. 
</P>
