<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER HITS LIGHT POLE, CUTS POWER TO RESIDENCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The driver of a green Cadillac delivered a knockout blow to a sturdy light pole 
early Saturday, cutting off power to about 1,600 residences on the city's 
southwest side, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The Cadillac ran off the road at Placentia Avenue and 20th Street at 2:39 a.m. 
and sheared off the pole, downing electric lines and cutting power to 
residences for about an hour. 
</P>
<P>
And just as police thought they had the mess contained, another driver plowed 
through barricades set up at the intersection. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the Cadillac, Mario Rebolliar, 21, of Costa Mesa, and the other 
driver, Luis Fernandez, 25, also of Costa Mesa, were charged with driving under 
the influence of alcohol and were arrested at the scene. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Police could not estimate how fast the Cadillac was traveling at the time of 
impact, but Police Lt. Gary Webster said: 
</P>
<P>
"It had to be putting along pretty good to knock one of those poles off." 
</P>
<P>
Although power was restored in the area, Webster said it will take at least 24 
hours to install a new pole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; POWER FAILURES -- ORANGE COUNTY; DRUNK 
DRIVING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092390-0231 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 282021 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 23, 1990, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
